t","score":34,"flags":2,"comment_count":8,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"hongminhee","user_is_author":true,"tags":["javascript"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cpyxnw","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cpyxnw/i_wish_deno_would_keep_doing_what_it_does"},{"short_id":"qgy6ak","created_at":"2026-06-08T10:12:16.000-05:00","title":"Can we stop tagging every thing as vibecoding?","url":"","score":159,"flags":3,"comment_count":91,"description":"\u003cp\u003eAny article that even slightly mentions that AI exists is tagged as vibecoding, even when they have nothing to do with it. It:s getting out of hand.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 1:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTagged as vibecoding, article contains a \u003cem\u003esingle\u003c/em\u003e passing reference\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ewhere people are racing to create intelligent machines, but only in order to make them slaves\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 2 (my own article; biased)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI quoted a \u003cem\u003eSINGLE\u003c/em\u003e example of someone putting an agentic spin on an old trope:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\"Users don’t care whether the code was written by AI or by hand, or which framework you used. They care that the product works.\"\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 3\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a code repo. There is no AGENTS.md, or CLAUDE.md, or any mention of AI in the readme...\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEXAMPLE 4:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis post, which someone will inevitably tag as \"vibecoding\"\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Any article that even slightly mentions that AI exists is tagged as vibecoding, even when they have nothing to do with it. It:s getting out of hand.\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 1:\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/ly0vif/my_students\r\n\r\nTagged as vibecoding, article contains a *single* passing reference\r\n\r\n\u003e  where people are racing to create intelligent machines, but only in order to make them slaves\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 2 (my own article; biased)\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/vufbvv/user_doesn_t_care_you_should\r\n\r\nI quoted a *SINGLE* example of someone putting an agentic spin on an old trope:\r\n\r\n\u003e \"Users don’t care whether the code was written by AI or by hand, or which framework you used. They care that the product works.\"\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 3\r\n\r\nhttps://lobste.rs/s/gefcox/jolt_clojure_interpreter_on_janet\r\n\r\nThis is a code repo. There is no AGENTS.md, or CLAUDE.md, or any mention of AI in the readme...\r\n\r\nEXAMPLE 4:\r\n\r\nthis post, which someone will inevitably tag as \"vibecoding\"","submitter_user":"LAC-Tech","user_is_author":true,"tags":["meta","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qgy6ak","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qgy6ak/can_we_stop_tagging_every_thing_as"},{"short_id":"dvcyyz","created_at":"2026-06-09T07:24:02.000-05:00","title":"Looking Forward to Postgres 19: Query Hints","url":"https://www.pgedge.com/blog/looking-forward-to-postgres-19-query-hints","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"rslabbert","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dvcyyz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dvcyyz/looking_forward_postgres_19_query_hints"},{"short_id":"qa5xds","created_at":"2026-06-09T04:10:50.000-05